If you own a custom domain and want the site at that domain instead of
universalherbalcare-bk.github.io/master-microstructure-decode-format/, rename
this file to CNAME (no extension) and put your domain on the first line, e.g.:

decode.yourdomain.com

Then add a DNS CNAME record at your domain registrar pointing that subdomain
to universalherbalcare-bk.github.io, and update every "universalherbalcare-bk.github.io/..."
URL in index.html, sitemap.xml, and robots.txt to your custom domain.
